clear%20a%20wider%20area%20in%20less%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Yahoodain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiles%20per%20hour%20(MPH)%20refers%20to%20the%20speed%20of%20the%20air%20coming%20out%20of%20the%20blower.%20Yahoodain%20explains%20that%20you%20can%20maximize%20this%20speed%20by%20using%20different%20sizes%20and%20shapes%20of%20nozzles.%20An%20open%2C%20circular%20nozzle%20allows%20more%20air%20to%20come%20out%20at%20once%2C%20while%20a%20wider%2C%20tapered%20nozzle%20will%20give%20you%20more%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20do%20you%20use%20a%20leaf%20blower%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20just%20wander%20out%20into%20the%20yard%20and%20start%20blowing%2C%20you're%20probably%20going%20to%20waste%20time%20and%20energy.%20Having%20a%20strategy%20in%20place%20ensures%20that%20you're%20working%20efficiently%20and%20won't%20waste%20time%20covering%20the%20same%20areas%20over%20and%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETo%20avoid%20doubling%20up%20on%20work%20areas%2C%20you%20need%20to%20designate%20a%20collection%20point%20for%20your%20leaves%20or%20debris.%20This%20is%20typically%20the%20center%20of%20the%20yard%2C%20preferably%20on%20a%20large%20tarp.%20If%20your%20work%20area%20is%20really%20big%2C%20separate%20it%20into%20sections%2C%20each%20with%20its%20own%20collection%20point.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBeginning%20at%20the%20perimeter%2C%20use%20your%20blower%20to%20push%20the%20leaves%20towards%20the%20center%20of%20the%20yard%20in%20broad%20strokes%2C%20working%20your%20way%20around%20the%20yard.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUse%20low%20shallow%20strokes%20and%20adjust%20the%20power%20of%20the%20blower%20as%20you%20get%20closer%20to%20the%20center.%20Don't%20stress%20over%20every%20single%20leaf.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOnce%20your%20leaves%20and%20debris%20are%20collected%2C%20use%20the%20tarp%20to%20funnel%20them%20into%20a%20yard%20waste%20bag%20or%20use%20them%20in%20a%20compost%20pile.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20loud%20are%20leaf%20blowers%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ELeaf%20blowers%20are%20notoriously%20loud%20machines%20and%20can%20generate%20enough%20noise%20to%20cause%20significant%20hearing%20loss%20over%20time.%20It's%20possible%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnceh%2Fhearing_loss%2Fwhat_noises_cause_hearing_loss.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edamage%20your%20hearing%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%20a%20leaf%20blower%20with%20a%20noise%20rating%20of%2080%20decibels%20and%20above%20for%20two%20hours%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20operating%20a%20leaf%20blower%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20wear%20ear%20protection.%20Two%20of%20our%20picks%2C%20the%C2%A0Husqvarna%20350BT%C2%A0and%20the%C2%A0Worx%20WG520%20Turbine%2C%C2%A0are%20over%2080%20dB(A)%2C%20so%20take%20that%20into%20consideration%20when%20choosing%20your%20blower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EAre%20leaf%20blowers%20bad%20for%20the%20environment%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EElectric%20blowers%2C%20both%20corded%20and%20battery-powered%2C%20don't%20directly%20generate%20emissions%2C%20as%20gas-powered%20models%20do.%20If%20an%20electric%20blower%20can%20meet%20your%20needs%2C%20there's%20no%20need%20to%20choose%20a%20gas-powered%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20lessen%20the%20harmful%20effects%20of%20your%20gas-powered%20blower%2C%20always%20make%20sure%20they%20are%20rated%20as%20CARB-compliant.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fww2.arb.ca.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalifornia%20Air%20Resources%20Board%3C%2Fa%3E%20regulates%20outdoor%20landscaping%20emissions%20and%20rates%20equipment%20as%20CARB-compliant%20only%20if%20their%20emissions%20fall%20below%20a%20certain%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EAre%20gas-powered%20leaf%20blowers%20restricted%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20set%20on%20purchasing%20a%20gas-powered%20blower%2C%20make%20sure%20to%20check%20for%20any%20restrictions%20or%20regulations%20in%20your%20area.%20Hundreds%20of%20cities%20across%20the%20country%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhdsupplysolutions.com%2Fs%2Fleaf_blower_noise_regulation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20passed%20legislation%3C%2Fa%3E%20limiting%20the%20use%20of%20gas-powered%20leaf%20blowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20has%20taken%20the%20strictest%20stances%20against%20them%2C%20with%2016%20cities%20that%20have%20banned%20gas-powered%20blowers%20altogether.%20According%20to%20CARB%2C%20some%20cities%20have%20even%20introduced%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fww2.arb.ca.gov%2Four-work%2Fprograms%2Fzero-emission-landscaping-equipment%2Fzero-emission-landscaping-equipment-incentive%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade-in%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20incentivize%20people%20to%20switch%20to%20electric%20lawn%20care%20equipment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20District%20of%20Columbia%20instituted%20a%20complete%20ban%20on%20gas-powered%20leaf%20blowers%20on%20January%201%2C%202022.%20The%20nationwide%20push%20towards%20all-electric%20lawn%20equipment%20doesn't%20appear%20to%20be%20slowing%20down%20anytime%20soon%2C%20so%20even%20if%20you're%20not%20in%20an%20area%20affected%20today%2C%20that%20may%20change%20in%20the%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-leaf-blower%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726090453000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653682b40487ff031caba3db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-leaf-blower%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Professional%20landscapers%20helped%20us%20narrow%20down%20the%20best%20leaf%20blowers%2C%20including%20powerful%20and%20user-friendly%20electric%2C%20battery-powered%2C%20and%